-- AT&T says no longer pursuing Olimpia stake
-- 
-- Mon Apr 16, 2007 2:30pm EDT
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2007/04/16/us-att-telecomitalia-pullout-idUSWNAS640020070416

 

 NEW YORK  (Reuters) - Top U.S. phone company AT&T Inc. ( T.N ) said on Monday it would no longer pursue a stake in Olimpia, which controls Italy's largest telecoms company Telecom Italia ( TLIT.MI ). 

 AT&T said in a statement that it ended negotiations to acquire a one-third stake in Olimpia, and that it has "decided not to pursue the matter further."